news.title: Abu Dhabi's Aldar Properties posts 54% jump in profit in Apr-June 2022
news.para: Profit attributable to shareholders came in at 803.99 million dirhams ($218.91 million) for the three months to June 30, compared with 520.83 million dirhams a year earlier.

news.title: Sundaram Home Finance posts net profit of Rs 47.26 crore in Q1 FY23
news.para: Disbursements during the quarter under review grew to Rs 796 crore from Rs 249 crore registered same quarter previous year, a company statement said here.

news.title: China Evergrande gets bid from CK Asset for Hong Kong headquarters building
news.para: With more than $300 billion in liabilities, Evergrande has been trying to sell its 26-storey China Evergrande Centre in Hong Kong's Wan Chai district after a potential $1.7 billion deal collapsed late last year, as part of the asset disposal effort to raise fund.

news.title: China targets $148 billion in financing for cash-strapped developers
news.para: The People's Bank of China (PBOC) will initially issue about 200 billion yuan of low-interest loans, charging about 1.75% a year, to state commercial banks, the FT said, citing people involved in the discussions.

news.title: PNB Housing Finance net profit dips 3.4% to Rs 235 crore in April-June
news.para: Revenues in the first quarter of FY23 were down at Rs 1,412 crore as against Rs 1,693 crore in the year-ago period, PNB Housing Finance said in a regulatory filing.

news.title: Asia's richest woman loses half her wealth in China property crisis
news.para: Yang Huiyan, a majority shareholder in Chinese property giant Country Garden, saw her net worth plunge by more than 52 percent to $11.3 billion from $23.7 billion a year ago, according to the Bloomberg Billionaires Index.

news.title: Shree Cement's net profit falls 55.8% to Rs 278.86 crore in Q1 FY23
news.para: However, its revenue from operations increased 21.45 per cent to Rs 4,414.85 crore during the quarter under review against Rs 3,634.83 crore in the corresponding period of the preceding fiscal.

news.title: Saint-Gobain posts record operating income, confident can offset inflation
news.para: Its operating income hit a new record in the half-year, reaching 2.80 billion euros, up 13% on last year at constant exchange rates.

news.title: Jaipur development body's high regularisation rates invite protests from residents
news.para: On Wednesday, a delegation from Moti Nagar met Jaipur development commissioner Ravi Jain and demanded reduction of the rates from Rs 2,500 to Rs 200.

news.title: Hong Kong home prices fall to the lowest in 18 months in June 2022
news.para: Home prices in one of the world's most unaffordable housing markets slipped 1.1% last month from a month earlier, compared with a revised 0.2% decline in May.

news.title: Jaisalmer: 18 dilapidated houses in Sonar Fort razed
news.para: ​The administration said there was a possibility of damages to lives and properties in houses situated near the locked, dilapidated houses in the fort during heavy rains.

news.title: Kolkata: E-mutation for Rajarhat-Gopalpur properties soon
news.para: BMC MMiC Debraj Chakraborty said that e-mutation camps will be held for residents living in Rajarhat Gopalpur sideto help them with any of their queries.

news.title: Property possession hurdle for Pune civic body in 11 merged villages
news.para: The civic administration has got these properties on paper from the respective gram panchayats and the district administration.

news.title: Thrikkakara municipality council recommends cancellation of building permit
news.para: Meanwhile, the council approved the recommendation of the finance standing committee to issue notices to owners of buildings which were expanded without the permission of the local body and regularize it after collecting a fine amount.

news.title: HC restrains Chennai civic body from collecting hiked property tax
news.para: When the matter came up on July 25, the Corporation Standing Counsel circulated a Council resolution dated May 30, 2022 of the GCC, which was based on a GO dated March 30 this year, and a consequent notification dated April 11, 2022.
